# Getting Started with {{.Name}}

## Quick Start

1. Install {{.Name}} (see [install](install.md))

2. Initialize a new project:
   ```sh
   {{.Name}} init
   ```

3. Run your first command:
   ```sh
   {{.Name}} help
   ```

## Basic Usage

```sh
# Show help
{{.Name}} --help

# Show version
{{.Name}} --version

# Run with verbose output
{{.Name}} --verbose <command>
```

## Configuration

{{.Name}} looks for configuration in:

1. `./{{.Name}}.yaml` (project-local)
2. `~/.config/{{.Name}}/config.yaml` (user)
3. Environment variables prefixed with
   `{{.Name}}_` (uppercase)

See [configuration](configuration.md) for details.

